 @jesseschutz1505  A lot of the best electronic music wasn't even released by Madonna, but by William Orbit, for example, who'd produced much of Madonna's "Ray of Light" album. Check out "Water From a Wine Leaf" and its remix, the one with green leaves as default picture here on YouTube.

Other electronic greats of the time were The Crystal Method, Front Line Assembly ("Millennium", "Implode", "Epitaph", and "Cryogenic Studios" albums), and I'd also add Nine Inch Nails.

NIN and Front Line Assembly still hold up very well, and FLA's music from 20+ years ago is timeless and futuristic even now. If often angry and very somber.

